Spritz is an independent clean-room Python implementation inspired by public
atmospheric puff-modeling workflows and file roles. It does not contain,
translate, embed, or redistribute proprietary Fortran source code, executables,
manuals, sample data, or parameter tables from third-party modeling suites.
Spritz, SpritzWRF, SpritzMet, Terrain, Spritz, and SpritzPost name the
clean-room components in this project.
